body:
@Jackie-Jiang we already replaced that expensive API call with this one 
https://github.com/apache/pinot/pull/11793
https://github.com/apache/pinot/pull/11576

@Jackie-Jiang , we have a lot of existing customers using this kind of query and asking them to rewrite the query takes non-trivial effort. This is blocking our Pinot 0.12 version upgrade in Uber.

Could we safely revert #9605 or make minimum change to keep the old behavior in 0.12+ release while working with customers to migrate the queries for the long run?
Also it seems in current master branch, using the multi-stage engine will work with the old behavior on the non aggregation group by, is this intended? In 0.12.1 this will not work for multi-stage engine either. Does anyone know which PR made multi-stage engine working with the old behavior?
